$15.00 https://doi.org/10.1145/3359789.33598481 INTRODUCTION MATE refers to a class of adversaries whose access to the soft- ware execution environment allows them to monitor, subvert, and tamper with any running program in that environment [ 25].
ASPIRE project (https://aspire-fp7.eu/) is a framework that en- ables chaining of integrity protection techniques.
We use the lemon graph library (https://lemon.cs.elte.hu), due to its performance and flexibility, to build our defense graph with specialized arcs and nodes.
We use glpk library (https://www.gnu.org/software/glpk/) to solve the linear problem.

The other three programs in our dataset are open-source games snake (https://github.com/ troglobit/snake), tetris (https://github.com/troglobit/tetris) and 2048 (https://github.com/cuadue/2048_game) taken from GitHub.
To cope with this problem, in the generation of protected instances of the aforementioned programs, we utilize the commer- cialGurobi solver (http://www.gurobi.com/) under a free academic license.
